        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 12 at 7:28PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 728 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of thunderstorms
extending from 28 miles east of Miles City to 20 miles west of
Biddle, or extending from 28 miles east of Miles City to 28 miles
southwest of Broadus, moving east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Miles City, Baker, Broadus, Ekalaka, Ridgeway, Volborg, Biddle,
Alzada, Plevna, Ismay, Powderville, Mizpah, Knowlton, Boyes,
Medicine Rocks State Park, Olive, Hammond, Belltower, Belle Creek
and Locate.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
